videos.description: Michigan's Muhammad-Ali Abdur-Rahkman takes the feed from Zavier Simpson in transition, drives to the rim and throws down a one-handed hammer.

videos.description: Penn State's Tony Carr puts the moves on his defender, spins and tosses a nice pass to Julian Moore who takes advantage of the dish with a two-handed slam.

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Carr's nifty moves set up Moore for a PSU jam) 2018/02/21 ESHEET

videos.description: Zavier Simpson sends a nice dish from the top of the arc to Duncan Robinson who goes up-and-under for the bucket.
videos.headline: Michigan's Robinson impressing under the rim

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Michigan's Robinson impressing under the rim) 2018/02/21 ESHEET

videos.description: Off the steal, Michigan's Jordan Poole attacks the rim with a one-handed slam and celebrates with an epic stare down.

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Poole rocks the rim, stares down the camera) 2018/02/21 ESHEET

videos.description: Tony Carr pumps up the crowd with his triple from the corner after Michigan left him open in the second half.
videos.headline: Carr drains wide-open 3-pointer

videos.description: Lamar Stevens comes up with a massive rejection on Michigan at one end of the court setting Tony Carr up at the other end for an and-1 bucket.
videos.headline: Stevens' swat sets up Carr for and-1 bucket for Nittany Lions

videos.description: Former high school teammates, Tony Carr and Lamar Stevens team-up for a rim-rocking alley-oop against Michigan that amps up the crowd.

videos.description: Holding a four-point lead, Muhammad-Ali Abdur-Rahkman gets his shot to fall and after a missed shot on the other end, Duncan Robinson drains a 3-pointer to put Michigan up nine.
videos.headline: Pair of clutch Michigan shots puts Penn State away

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Pair of clutch Michigan shots puts Penn State away) 2018/02/21 ESHEET

videos.description: Zavier Simpson's drives into the paint, makes the best of his Penn State defenders and hits a wild shot in the second half.
videos.headline: Michigan's Simpson hits NBA-like hook shot

videos.description: No. 17 Michigan pulls away late in the second half to defeat conference-rival Penn State, behind Duncan Robinson's 19 points off the bench and Moritz Wagner's 18.
videos.headline: Michigan holds off Penn State
